[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_2nt_splinters"]
[Student "S"]
{You have a great hand, but no singleton to show. Since you have a 6-card \H suit you bid 3\H. Partner replies 3\S.  

Partner has control-bid the \SA. He may also have one or both of the Minor Aces since he would have bid the cheapest control first. You use Blackwood. He replies 5\D.  

Oops. Despite all the points you are missing two Aces. So you thank Mr. Blackwood and sign off at 5\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "S:AQ853.5.AJT72.63 T4.Q62.94.QT9742 K9762.AK74.KQ8.K J.JT983.653.AJ85"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "6S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1S pass 2NT pass 4D pass 4NT pass 5H pass 6S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "6273957b4cec394bcdb5ec40836c28192273fb7a66e700212f39de6fa1a9668c"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/jacoby_2nt_splinters"]
[Student "S"]
{You don't want to make a Splinter Bid with a singleton King so you content yourself with a Jacoby 2NT bid. Partner rebids 4\D. What do you say next? 

The 4\D bid shows a 5-card \D suit. What you need to know now is how many Aces partner has. You bid 4NT and he answers 5\H.  

He has two Aces so you bid 6\S.}

